               <msContents>
                  <summary>Substantial sections from an illustrated treatise titled Book of the balance of wisdom, which concerns measurement of weight, with a historical introduction to theories of gravity and weighing in Greek and Arabic science; tables of densities of substances including metals, precious stones, solids, and liquids; and descriptions of different types of balances. A few marginal notes are present. A few catchwords and some minuscule letters under undotted letters have been added by later hands. Damage to edges of many leaves.</summary>
                  <textLang>Arabic</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <title>Kitāb Mīzān al-ḥikmah</title>
                     <author>Khāzinī, ʻAbd al-Raḥmān, fl. 1121</author>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
